profile_positions.description:
-- Manages the team of six Regulatory specialists in Western European countries prioritizing the work as aligned with the European marketing calendar;
- Coordinates the registrations of Diversey’s products positioned as disinfectants and other biocidal products by preparing registration files in collaboration with internal product development to ensure successful authorizations;
- Submits and follows up on submitted BPR dossiers. In case of questions or  challenges, finds acceptable solutions for Diversey as well as the European competent authorities;
- Maintains in-depth knowledge of relevant regulations and guidance, monitors new
regulatory developments, identifies potential impact on the product portfolio;
- Partners with R&D, Marketing and Commercialisation teams to give input into successful innovation designs and product implementations;
- Help to manage Diversey’s global chemicals portfolio and ensures alignment with strategy according to the annual plans of Diversey.
- Collaborates on budget planning of the Regulatory department.

- Leads and organizes complex intra- and inter-departmental (cross-functional) project teams addressing key business needs with assigned resources;
- Ensure complex master registration dossiers for biocides (BPR and transitional period) meet the business and authorization requisites in claims and timing;
- Participation in Innovation projects acting as the Regulatory representative, guiding team members and helping them tackle possible issues ahead of time; 
- Maintains and grows the regulatory intelligence network in selected European countries by interacting with business leads and trade associations;
- Helps to manage Diversey’s global chemicals portfolio and ensure alignment with chemical strategy according to the annual and strategic plans of Diversey;
- Represents Diversey at competent authority and industry meetings and giving external presentations;
- Mentors regulatory compliance specialists on their regulatory projects, processes, and issues;
- Coordinates and reviews actions outsourced to the global regulatory service center in relation to registrations;
- Helps budget planning within the Regulatory team, managing SAP Ariba purchase orders.

- Responsible for coordinating pre-BPR registrations within European countries, ensuring to meet business and authorization requirements in claims in a timely manner;
- Maintenance o and growth of the regulatory intelligence network by interacting with authorities and trade associations;
- Support to managing global portfolio and alignment with biocides strategy and stakeholders according to annual and strategic plans;
-	 Review of BPR dossiers and their compliance, working in alignment with the business and customer needs;
-	 Organization of regular compliance checks, working closely with Marketing and Sales Planners;
-	 Participation in Innovation projects by giving regulatory input, tackling possible issues ahead of time; 
-	 Maintenance of regulatory databases and the lifecycle of products with the use of the softwares UL WERCSmart and Agile PLM.
- Creation of purchase orders for the Regulatory team, making sure to stick to the planned budget by using SAP Ariba.

●  Elaboration of dossiers for registration and post registration of fungicides to federal regulatory agencies (MAPA, ANVISA and IBAMA) in compliance with the current legislation;
●	State Registration and Inerts Registration Focal Point in the team, being resposible for coordinating everything related to these areas, meeting demands of Marketing, Sales, Operations and Sourcing under tight deadlines;
● Representation of DuPont in COLEM (Committee of State and Municipal Legislation) monthly meetings at SINDIVEG;
●	Evaluation of the studies which compose the technical dossier for pesticides federal registration;
●    Periodic review of the MSDS of the products active in the portfolio;	
●	Review of the check-list for request of EUP (Experimental Use Permit) for fungicides;

● Responsible  for submission, update and renewal of dossiers of State Registration of pesticides and FUP with the regulatory agencies, according to the necessity of Marketing and Sales areas;
● Representation of DuPont in COLEM (Committee of State and Municipal Legislation) monthly meetings at Andef (National Association of Plant Protection);
● Responsible for the Inerts Registration of pesticides, according the demands of local and global Sourcing and Operations areas;
● 5 Batch Studies Focal Point in Brazil, orienting the global teams of the requirements regarding those studies;

● Support to the Registration and Regulatory Affairs team in the following activities:

 - Elaboration of processes of registration and post registration to be submitted to federal regulatory agencies (MAPA, ANVISA and IBAMA);
- Review of studies which compound the technical dossier of pesticides federal registration;
- Review of leaflets and labels of the whole portfolio of formulated products.
- Regulatory Intelligence, by monitoring the progress of processes of registration post registration in the analysis queue of MAPA, ANVISA and IBAMA;
- Elaboration and Maintenance of EUP (Emergency Use Permit) processes ;
- Classification of Import Samples for experimentation, according to NCM (Standard of Classification of Goods)
